cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.ME, cs.ET, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the design of Series Elastic Actuators (SEAs) for an ankle prosthesis, which is a common application in robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a non-parametric convex optimization program for the design of the nonlinear elastic element that minimizes energy consumption and peak power for an arbitrary periodic reference trajectory. This is a control problem that falls under the scope of cs.SY. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper discusses the design of SEAs, which is a topic that is relevant to mechanical engineering. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): SEAs are a relatively new technology that has gained popularity in recent years, and this paper contributes to the development of this technology. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a convex optimization framework for the design of SEAs, which involves computational methods and techniques.
